<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62ddc70b-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s5208"><num value="5208">§ 5208.</num><heading> Application of provisions to Osage County</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This chapter shall not relate to or affect Osage County, Oklahoma.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id62ddc70c-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1936-06-26/ch831/s8">June 26, 1936, ch. 831, § 8</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/49/1968">49 Stat. 1968</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id62ddc70d-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id62ddc70e-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id62ddc70f-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t25/s508">section 508 of this title</ref> prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
